OL,3,CSpecialist drugs and alcohol court
OL,4,Cneeded to 'scratch surface' of crime
OL,6,FFamily law barrister Helen Scourfield,
OL,7,Fwho organised the conference, told ITV
OL,8,FTyne Tees: "The issue of gangs, drugs,
OL,9,Fknife crime, shootings is becoming an
OL,10,Fincreasing problem and we need to do
OL,11,Fsomething to tackle it.
OL,13,F"We need to scratch the surface with
OL,14,Fthese young people. Quite often they
OL,15,Fwon't engage with professionals
OL,16,Fbecause they have done for years and
OL,17,Fit hasn't made any difference.
OL,19,F"The hope is that we can engage with
OL,20,Fthese young people so they can see
OL,21,Fthat there are other options."
